253
00:17:47,623 --> 00:17:50,246
but for some reason, I couldn't move my body.

254
00:17:50,984 --> 00:17:51,663
That's right.

255
00:17:52,343 --> 00:17:53,887
I may not have been able to move,

256
00:17:53,921 --> 00:17:55,556
but I remember everything.

257
00:17:56,211 --> 00:17:59,512
That sweet little boy devoted himself to protecting me

258
00:18:00,093 --> 00:18:02,906
and risked his life by fighting against a grown man.

259
00:18:03,405 --> 00:18:05,461
He had such a brave and heroic heart.

260
00:18:05,913 --> 00:18:07,516
Oh, where did that boy go?

261
00:18:08,168 --> 00:18:11,230
Where... where did my little knight run off to?

262
00:18:12,759 --> 00:18:15,155
Where did you go? Where are you?!

263
00:18:18,191 --> 00:18:20,915
I've never met such an amazing woman before,

264
00:18:21,051 --> 00:18:23,373
so kind, so genuine.

265
00:18:24,313 --> 00:18:25,415
That was a close one,

266
00:18:25,445 --> 00:18:27,766
but thankfully I'm back to my normal self.

267
00:18:28,542 --> 00:18:30,254
I wonder if she's okay.

268
00:18:30,943 --> 00:18:31,449
Hmm?

269
00:18:36,754 --> 00:18:39,407
Uh, uh, I hate to bother you,

270
00:18:39,467 --> 00:18:43,995
but you didn't happen to see a sweet, little boy
leave my house in something of a hurry, did you?

271
00:18:44,414 --> 00:18:45,708
He has silver hair.

272
00:18:46,383 --> 00:18:48,929
Come to think of it, it looks exactly like yours.

273
00:18:57,846 --> 00:18:59,227
Pardon me for asking,

274
00:18:59,252 --> 00:19:01,241
but have the two of us met before?

275
00:19:06,368 --> 00:19:08,181
No, I didn't see a kid come through.

276
00:19:08,638 --> 00:19:10,103
Sorry I couldn't help you.

277
00:19:10,331 --> 00:19:11,656
Let's go, Jotaro.

278
00:19:14,562 --> 00:19:15,863
Come on. Hurry up.

279
00:19:16,117 --> 00:19:18,378
Uh, wa... please wait!

280
00:19:19,184 --> 00:19:20,064
Could you be...

281
00:19:20,680 --> 00:19:22,077
That earring you're wearing...

282
00:19:24,001 --> 00:19:26,100
The two of us have never met before.

283
00:19:26,702 --> 00:19:27,910
It's not possible.

284
00:19:28,563 --> 00:19:32,590
My friend and I are travelers, so if you'll excuse us,

285
00:19:32,723 --> 00:19:34,598
there's another town we need to get to.

286
00:19:35,182 --> 00:19:36,448
We'll be going now.

287
00:19:41,915 --> 00:19:43,435
It was only a dream.

288
00:19:44,198 --> 00:19:45,108
Too bad.

289
00:19:52,380 --> 00:19:54,605
Not a single word from you, Jotaro.

290
00:19:54,714 --> 00:19:56,013
I don't wanna hear it.

291
00:20:02,530 --> 00:20:05,509
Oh! Jotaro and Polnareff!

292
00:20:06,015 --> 00:20:08,463
Where in the world have you two slackers been?!

293
00:20:08,601 --> 00:20:11,026
Ah! Mr. Joestar and Avdol!

294
00:20:12,027 --> 00:20:15,763
How many times have I told the two of
you not to go wandering off on your own?

295
00:20:15,795 --> 00:20:17,364
Oh, you're in a position to talk!

296
00:20:17,398 --> 00:20:19,258
You're the ones who just disappeared!

297
00:20:19,600 --> 00:20:20,260
Eh...

298
00:20:20,303 --> 00:20:21,287
Now, now.

299
00:20:21,408 --> 00:20:23,663
Why don't we focus on getting something to eat?

300
00:20:24,083 --> 00:20:25,393
Huh? Hey, Iggy!

301
00:20:25,463 --> 00:20:27,396
Where the hell have you been all day long?!

302
00:20:40,349 --> 00:20:41,689
Can I take that for you?

303
00:20:44,339 --> 00:20:46,234
Yeah, thanks a million.

304
00:20:47,229 --> 00:20:49,717
Eh, it's about time.

305
00:20:49,751 --> 00:20:51,482
We're finally getting a bit of relief.

306
00:20:51,635 --> 00:20:53,383
It was quite the late breakfast,

307
00:20:53,408 --> 00:20:55,272
but I suppose it couldn't be helped.

308
00:20:55,572 --> 00:20:56,247
Yeah.

309
00:20:56,632 --> 00:20:58,604
Since we've almost made it to Cairo,

310
00:20:58,668 --> 00:21:01,596
I think it's time we figured out where Dio is hiding out.

311
00:21:03,660 --> 00:21:05,220
Oh, we're doin' this?

312
00:21:05,493 --> 00:21:06,459
Will it appear?

313
00:21:06,529 --> 00:21:10,925
I'm not sure, but given that we're so
close, the results should be more precise.

314
00:21:11,225 --> 00:21:13,067
All right, here we go!

315
00:21:20,449 --> 00:21:23,066
Excuse me, sir. Is there a problem over here?

316
00:21:23,192 --> 00:21:25,390
Everything's fine. Mind your own business.

317
00:21:25,415 --> 00:21:27,011
Uh, yes, sir.

318
00:21:27,676 --> 00:21:30,019
Hmm.

319
00:21:31,001 --> 00:21:33,918
Old man, tell us. What is it?

320
00:21:34,229 --> 00:21:35,747
Just a little longer.

321
00:21:36,312 --> 00:21:39,874
I see something. It's getting clearer.

322
00:21:41,176 --> 00:21:41,749
Huh?

323
00:21:41,938 --> 00:21:43,162
Take a good look!

324
00:21:45,876 --> 00:21:48,529
There you have it, gentlemen, our final destination!

